PV Calculation & Scenario Analysis (PnL Monitoring)

Purpose: Compute current portfolio value and simulate PnL under different market scenarios (spot & volatility shocks).

1. Input data
* Load portfolio + reference Greeks + PnL sheet
* Clean and validate numeric inputs

2.1. Base Pricing (PV₀) (last 3 columns in calculated_price_{date}.xlsx)
a. Option pricing
* Call: bs_call_pricing(S, K, r, q, tau, sigma)
* Put: bs_put_pricing(S, K, r, q, tau, sigma)
* Meaning: theoretical option value using Black-Scholes

b. Future pricing
* Formula: F = Spot_fut × exp((r - q) × tau)
* Meaning: forward-adjusted price

c. Combine PV 
* Logic: use Call / Put / Future → fallback to market price
* Output: PV_0_VOL_0
* Signal: current fair value of each position

2.2. Scenario Generation (in pv_scenario_{date}.xlsx)
a. Shock grid
* Spot shifts: -10% → +10%
* Vol shifts: -5% → +5%

b. Repricing logic
* Recalculate price under each (spot, vol) combination
* Compute: Scenario PnL = (New Price - Base PV) × Position × FX

c. Special handling
* Options:
- Adjust both spot and volatility
- Handle intrinsic value if vol ≤ 0
* Futures:
- Only spot shift matters

d. Output 
* 2D grid of PnL scenarios per instrument

2.3. Aggregation & Sensitivity Tables (in sensitivity_tables_{date}.xlsx)
a. Group by underlying: Sum all positions per underlying asset

b. Matrix format 
* Rows: spot shocks
* Columns: volatility shocks

c. Total portfolio: Aggregate across all underlyings

d. Visualization - Apply color scale:
* Red = loss
* Green = gain
